cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

The paper deals with training spiking deep networks using LIF neurons for image classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also focuses on image classification, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the model, which could place it in cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the hope that the model can inform how the brain performs image classification, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for using neuromorphic hardware, which could place it in cs.SY (Systems and Control).
